comment: I'm just so friggin' tired of so many things at my job
Self serve up, lottery up.  All this work that needs to be done, and they demand be done, but not enough manpower to do it without a 7-hour cardio session.
My one coworker is a super hard worker, and she puts way more effort into this job than I'm willing to.  She will work herself into a sweat getting stuff done.
But I have literally 0 incentive to reward this BS

Because all that'll happen is, when the pandemic ends and they strip the extra work, they'll see that we were able to get our tasks "done" with the stripped hours, and reason that we can now get our old amount done with even less hours.
I hate complaining this much, but I'm between a rock and a hard place.

And even if I were to get laid off, I doubt I could collect unemployment.  I might not meet all the criteria.  Also that whole thing where there are so many claims coming in the whole system is locking up.
Okay, enough of that, let's switch speed

It's almost 11, the store closed at 10, I'm there late because I decided to finish one more task, btw not doing that again, before closing or nothing.
They're in front of the store, door's locked, lights at the pumps off, I'm finishing up closing out the register, phone starts ringing, I ignore it.
When it stops ringing, I just hear a car angrily accelerating away
I don't care if they talk to a manager tomorrow, because they'll probably be on my side.
Yeah seems good to keep with policy esp for your own safety that late.
My logic is, "If I didn't try finishing that one task, I probably would've been out of here a half-hour ago, and so you'd be calling an empty store
If anyone ever tries giving me shit for not finishing everything
I have the only response I'll ever need.
"Check the cameras. I :clap: DON'T :clap: TAKE :clap: BREAKS :clap: "
Feel free to criticize me for doing something wrong, I'll do it right in the future.  But I am constantly working these days.
